# 🌍 Nmap Host Discovery Scan (-sn)

## 🔹 Purpose
The **Nmap `-sn` scan** (also known as a *ping sweep*) is used to discover which hosts are alive in a given network range without scanning for open ports.  
It is helpful for quickly identifying active machines before performing detailed scans.

---

## 🔹 Command Used
```bash
nmap -sn 192.168.1.0/24
